gest home win           =\n  | biggest away win           =\n  | highest scoring            =\n  | longest wins               =\n  | longest unbeaten           =\n  | longest losses             =\n  | highest attendance         = [[Columbus Crew SC|Columbus Crew]]<br>Season: 283,129<br>Game Avg.: 17,696 \n  | lowest attendance          = [[Sporting Kansas City|Kansas City Wizards]]<br>Season: 130,924<br>Game Avg.: 8,183 \n  | attendance                 = 2,742,102\n  | average attendance         = 14,282\n  | prevseason                 = [[1998 Major League Soccer season|1998]]\n  | nextseason                 = [[2000 Major League Soccer season|2000]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1999 Major League Soccer season''' was the fourth season in [[Major League Soccer]]'s history. This was the last season which used the 35 yard line shootout rule to resolve tied games, and that of the countdown timer, with [[MLS Cup 1999]] adopting the IFAB-standard running clock thereafter.\n\n==Final standings==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!width=\"170\"|Eastern Conference\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| P | Played}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| W | Win}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip|(sw)|Shootout Win}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip|(sl)|Shootout Loss}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| L | Loss}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| GF | Goals for}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| GA | Goals against}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| GD | Goal difference}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| Pts | Points}}\n|-\n|align=left|s - [[D.C. United]]\n|32||23||6||3||9||65||43||+22||57\n|-\n|align=left|x - [[Columbus Crew]]\n|32||19||6||4||13||48||39||+9||45\n|-\n|align=left|x - [[Tampa Bay Mutiny]]\n|32||14||5||7||18||51||50||+1||32\n|-\n|align=left|x - [[Miami Fusion]]\n|32||13||5||4||19||42||59||\u201317||29\n|-\n|align=left|[[New England Revolution]]\n|32||12||5||7||20||38||53||\u201315||26\n|-\n|align=left|[[MetroStars]]\n|32||7||3||5||25||32||64||\u201332||15\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!width=\